# Hooten Young Dashboard — environment variables
#
# IMPORTANT:
#   - Vite exposes any var prefixed with VITE_* to the browser bundle.
#   - Anything in VITE_* is PUBLIC. Never put secrets there.
#   - True secrets stay on the backends (hooten-young-sales,
#     hooten-young-marketing) — this is a static SPA.
#
# How to use:
#   1. Copy this file to `.env.local` (gitignored) and fill in values.
#   2. In prod, the build pipeline injects these as docker --build-arg
#      values sourced from GitHub Environment Variables.

# --- Backend URLs (per domain) -----------------------------------
#
# The dashboard talks to two backends. Set the full origin (no trailing
# slash) of each Cloud Run service. Leave a value empty to use the
# Vite dev-server proxy (which routes /api/* to localhost:8000).

# Sales backend (handles /api/sales/* AND /api/depletions/*).
# Local dev (cross-origin):  VITE_SALES_API_URL=http://localhost:8000
# Dev environment example:   VITE_SALES_API_URL=https://hy-sales-api-dev-XXXX.run.app
VITE_SALES_API_URL=

# Marketing backend (handles /api/marketing/*). Owned by another team;
# leave empty until that backend is deployed.
VITE_MARKETING_API_URL=
